"Because I never taught you the hardest lesson," Asha replied. "The loom can create opportunities, but it cannot create willingness. Some chasms exist not in earth or water, but in choice."

She showed the student abandoned bridges throughout the land—perfect structures connecting people who chose separation. "Every weaver learns to read natural patterns: wind, water, earth. But human will? That pattern weaves itself."

"So we failed?" the student asked.

